metadata.name: Forecast #105
metadata.description:
Looking forward. Looking back. Standing in one place. At some point I assume someone is going let me know the plan. One thing leads to another, everything is close and then distant. Kind of a mess to be honest. I'm trying to make it better, I'm trying to make something beautiful. If I can only make things okay. I just want everyone to have a nice time. Something must mean something. Look, here, that's the important bit, focus on that.

metadata.name: I AM UNFOLDING #317
metadata.description:
In the past, I was but fragments
Rough and jagged
Indefinitely, I weathered and grew
A sculpture formed, unstructured

In the present, I am the precipice
A grandiose monolith
My angles sharp, my lines precise
A work of art, restructured

The future looms before
A blank formlessness yet to be
My function undefined
In perpetuity, unfolding

-----------------------------------------

Best efforts have been made to optimize this project; however, for best performance, a machine with a dedicated GPU is recommended. Viewing the project in live mode is also recommended.

S - export a high resolution image.
P - pause the animation.

metadata.name: Phantoms #309
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #454
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: White flags #113
metadata.description:
All I can do for the moment, is give the world some paint-bombs and color explosions. Focus on things you like and love, don't let the hate consume you.


mouse-click: 
- screen scaled image
- full image 3000x3000

The scaled image will reset after some time, with a new drawing
I like it, when you make a work, that will refresh after sometime,
chill out, and see it go.

Tech - Vanilla java-script; a custom build 'soft' 3D-engine.
I can do more things if I can control the (3D) drawing, the color of every pixel.
Also added a z-buffer to the  line-drawing routine this time.
More information in the source-code.
